news.title: Chandigarh administration may convert plots for MLA flats into general housing
news.para: UT adviser Dharam Pal said Chandigarh Housing Board (CHB) officials were asked to send a final reminder to Punjab, Haryana and PGI, for depositing the advance within a specific period, otherwise the UT would move ahead with other options, including general housing scheme.

news.title: Signature Global files Rs 1,000-crore IPO papers with Sebi
news.para: ​The IPO will comprise a fresh issue of equity shares worth up to Rs 750 crore and an Offer for Sale (OFS) of up to Rs 250 crore, according to the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) filed on Tuesday.

news.title: After bribe plaints, Ghaziabad development body says junior engineers can't seal properties
news.para: The order, issued by GDA vice-chairperson and district magistrate RK Singh, said junior engineers and supervisors cannot seal or de-seal a property without taking permission from the officer on special duty (OSD-enforcement) Sushil Kumar Choubey or the vice-chairperson’s office.

news.title: Government departments owe over Rs 16 crore in property tax to Dehradun civic body
news.para: According to sources at the DMC, various departments and institutions in Dehradun are yet to pay their housing tax. Officials said that the defaulters owe more than Rs 16 crore in taxes.

news.title: Lucknow: Pay heavy fine for wrong info in property tax self-assessment
news.para: The decision was taken after discussing the modalities of the software. The trial of the software began at LMC office on Tuesday. It will be launched soon.

news.title: Odisha lowers home loan interest rate to 8% for government staff
news.para: ​Since 2010, the employees were eligible for loans up to Rs 25 lakh. There were different interest rates depending on the loan taken, varying from 6% (for a loan up to Rs 50,000) to 11.5% (for Rs 25 lakh).

news.title: GST hike to nullify progress of last eight years: LED makers
news.para: LED lamp manufacturers including Bajaj, Havells and Century said the rate hike would widen the gap between inefficient bulbs and LED lamps and slow down the transition.

news.title: SC sets aside NCDRC order directing allottee to pay maintenance charges to DLF
news.para: A bench of Justices Dinesh Maheshwari and Aniruddha Bose said the entity (Condominium Association) to whom such charge is due has not raised any claim.

news.title: Google takes 1.3 million sq ft of office space in Bengaluru on lease: Sources
news.para: The California-headquartered company has entered into an agreement with Bagmane Developers for a new lease at its Bagmane Rio Business Park on Outer Ring Road, they told ET, adding that the property has a lease tenure of 15 years and is expected to be operational by the third quarter of 2022.

news.title: Nearly 6,000 Amrapali homebuyers have not cleared dues
news.para: Appearing before a bench of Justices U U Lalit and Bela Trivedi, senior advocate and the court’s receiver, R Venkataramani, said 3,338 flats had been constructed and 1,186 buyers took possession, but 700 buyers were not turning up to take possession.

news.title: SAT sets aside SEBI order to impose Rs 7 lakh fine: Jaypee Infratech
news.para: ​In a regulatory filing, Jaypee Infratech said the Securities and Exchange Board of India (SEBI) had passed an adjudication order on March 14, 2022 regarding disclosures required to be made to the stock exchanges.

news.title: Joyville Shapoorji Housing to invest Rs 700 crore in land acquisition
news.para: The company has deployed close to Rs 1,000 crore and the balance of Rs 240 crore will also be deployed in Pune, where it is in advance talks for an acquisition. Funds from this platform are used only for land acquisition and construction, and have been backed up by either construction finance, which it has raised, or by the customer advances the company receives.

news.title: Irregularities in allotment of Amritsar plots: Punjab vigilance bureau
news.para: A press release issued by the bureau said during the probe, evidence was found of alleged connivance of officers and employees of AIT in the allotment of commercial and residential plots.

news.title: Lodha Developers to invest Rs 3,950 crore over 5-7 years on sustainability initiatives
news.para: Lodha said: "Over the next five to seven years, we will be spending almost USD 500 million to ensure that our developments are moving to the net-zero carbon goal that we have".

news.title: PE investment in Indian real estate touch Rs 56 billion in Q2 2022: Savills India
news.para: As per the data, much like the previous quarter, commercial office assets continued to claim the lion’s share, of the PE investment during Q2 2022.
